                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3151</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-06T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 2, 6 p.m. Department has no funds at its disposal for maintenance of
                    refugees while in this country. You will make this clear to them. You are
                    authorized to furnish transportation to absolutely destitute Americans.
                    Transports or other vessels will be sent to Tampico in case of emergency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
